{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a84955a8-0be5-4a9d-ad34-aa1b23fe0ac4","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9.0, which supports all the modern patterns. Here's the recommended approach:\n\n**Constructor** for sync init + `TestContext` injection, **`[TestInitialize]`** for async init:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext injection via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = await CreateClientAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        _client?.Dispose();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` is the modern way (no more `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern).\n- `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` support `async Task`.\n- Constructor runs first (sync), then `[TestInitialize]` (async) — so split your setup accordingly.\n- You can also implement `IAsyncDisposable` as an alternative to `[TestCleanup]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74ae6a7a-5d85-4b85-8441-ac0b64865697","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. This is a modern version of MSTest (MSTest v3). Let me provide the recommended patterns.\n\nIn MSTest v3 (3.x), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use a constructor parameter or the `TestContext` property. In MSTest 3.x, constructor injection of `TestContext` is supported.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: `[TestInitialize]` supports `async Task` return type in MSTest v3.\n\n\n4. **Resource cleanup**: You can implement `IAsyncDisposable` or `IDisposable` for cleanup logic.\n\nThe most modern approach combines constructor injection for `TestContext` with an async `[TestInitialize]` method, and you can leverage disposal interfaces for cleanup when needed.","outputTokens":673,"requestId":"1BC1:345713:527B21:5DB6F0:6A03D793"},"id":"212f3b30-7318-4916-bfb7-b3ba4ff0d095","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:45:08.937Z","parentId":"977b17a6-8404-4f2a-862c-6e3d14791a39"}
